<br>
I am one of the raid leaders for an alliance of 7 (yes seven) guilds. We have a couple people at level 61, but only one higher.<br>
<br>
We went with about 36 people 58+ and a group of 53-57 (don't ask, I am too nice to some people LOL)<br>
<br>
I tanked him last night with ~6300 hps. I walked everyone through the encounter, using a PC to show positioning of Vindi, made everyone hit F9 to show where they were in the rainbow, we wedged him against a wall (not corner) with everyone and max melee range and kept him there.<br>
<br>
There was a modest amount of pushing. I lost agro once when he was pushed on top of me and the AM 2 ranger got whacked.<br>
<br>
But all in all, we went 5 sec Cheal chain. We had awesome clerics, I think my sister said she only used 3 cheals during the fight max. <br>
<br>
I popped disc on incoming. Ramp tank used bow to get 2nd agro with dedicated druid healer. <br>
<br>
I had on Mage 45 pt DS + 30 pt Shaman potion + 17? pt Bard DS (I think, confirming that now)<br>
<br>
Our monks single pulled him in about 12 minutes after they started trying. (Still wondering how they did that LOL) <br>
<br>
I had set up the information to do a Tank switch to our ~6150-6200 hp 2nd tank, sure to myself we would bork that up and die. <br>
<br>
I meleed for about 15 seconds, then called assist. Spam heals were coming in like a mofo. I am not exactly sure when the first cheal came in, but it was probably 10 seconds or so into my melee.<br>
<br>
I told the Debuff crew I wanted Debuffs 10 seconds after assist call. We did Tash, Malo, OOS and Cripple. I assume those all went fine. No one died (Maybe ench, trying to figure out who 2nd death was LOL)<br>
<br>
Nukers started in as Debuffs were going in.<br>
<br>
Way, Way too late to make this story short, We never needed a tank switch. It wasn't even close. I popped disc about 8 seconds before he even got their because I was so nervous and it still wasn't even close. I had about 5 seconds where I was down at 40% health, but spam healing covered it.<br>
<br>
We had one AM 2 ranger. We had one Rogue. We had one wizard (Level 56 lol) No GB. Rogue was level 53 with epic hehe.<br>
<br>
We brought about 43 to the fight total.<br>
<br>
Anyone else surprised by this result? <br>
<br>
A) I thought we were going to wipe a bunch of times. Anyone else have a crazy no problems type first ever Vindi fight?<br>
<br>
B) I thought our DPS was definitely lacking (No GB, One Rogue, One Wizard?) We do have a bunch of high level monks, though <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
C) Does this all rest on the fact that I just had a bunch (not telling you how many, you can figure it out from above) of REALLY great clerics? They were definitely heads-up and this is the FIRST time they have ever used Cheal Chain.<br>
<br>
D) Did I hold these guys back too long or what? I have been deathly afraid of Fooking up Vindicator. <br>
<br>
I know CR is easy, I even have a non-kos 56 cleric. I know you just need to do things in this game and learn painfully. I know that things get 10000x easier after you try them once.<br>
<br>
I just find it funny that we can screw up Queen of Chardok one week and then go destroy Vindicator the next. It's really tough getting 7 different guilds on the same page sometimes.<br>
<br>
So based on what you have read, is it time for RC and Va'dyn and Rhag 1 and Rhag 2 and DS and Named HoT and maybe even King Tormax? (3 Cheals used for 200k of Damage makes me hopeful - P.S. NO necros present and ONE bard LOL)<br>
<br>
I really love my alliance. Don't ask what happened to the boots. Some really interesting things happen when you have to be fair to all 7 guilds equally hehe.<br>
<br>
I am pretty proud. Thanks to all you guys for your advice and information. Tanking Vindicator and watching him go down like a sack of potatoes is something I have wanted to do for over a year.<br>
<br>
Thanks for listening to me wax poetic, and thanks for all the help guys.<br>
<br>
